 1177:         """
 1178:         Check whether we can safely convert a uint64 array to a numeric dtype.
 1179: 
 1180:         There are two cases when conversion to numeric dtype with a uint64
 1181:         array is not safe (and will therefore not be performed)
 1182: 
 1183:         1) A NaN element is encountered.
 1184: 
 1185:            uint64 cannot be safely cast to float64 due to truncation issues
 1186:            at the extreme ends of the range.
 1187: 
 1188:         2) A negative number is encountered.
 1189: 
 1190:            There is no numerical dtype that can hold both negative numbers
 1191:            and numbers greater than INT64_MAX. Hence, at least one number
 1192:            will be improperly cast if we convert to a numeric dtype.
 1193: 
 1194:         Returns
 1195:         -------
 1196:         bool
 1197:             Whether or not we should return the original input array to avoid
 1198:             data truncation.
 1199: 
 1200:         Raises
 1201:         ------
 1202:         ValueError
 1203:             uint64 elements were detected, and at least one of the
 1204:             two conflict cases was also detected. However, we are
 1205:             trying to force conversion to a numeric dtype.
 1206:         """
